title: Mother waits three years for answers after newborn's death | 7NEWS
description: A Western Australian mother waited three agonising years to learn why her newborn son Asha died at King Edward Memorial Hospital in 2020, due to severe backlogs at the coroner's office. The baby suffered catastrophic oxygen loss after an 11-minute delay in calling a code blue during delivery. Coronial reports taking over a year to release have increased by 30%, with the overall backlog now exceeding 1,000 cases despite calls for increased government funding. title: Ministers spend thousands on taxpayer-funded events | 7NEWS
description: Communications Minister Anika Wells spent approximately $9,000 on taxpayer-funded family attendance at three AFL grand finals since 2022, along with additional expenses including $4,000 for cricket events, $3,000 for a ski trip, $100,000 for New York flights, $27,000 for Paris and $42,000 for France and Switzerland trips. Trade Minister Don Farrell also spent about $9,000 attending sporting and cultural events including Opera House shows, Australian Open, AFL grand finals and a sunset dinner at Uluru. The Coalition is calling for a review of all political spending despite politicians from both sides justifying such expenses as being within existing rules. title: Manhunt underway after transformer vandalism in Moorbank | 7NEWS
description: Police are investigating suspected vandalism at an electricity transformer in Moorbank, Sydney's south-west, after the unit caught fire around 3:30am. Investigators found multiple tools and a single shoe at the scene, believing someone attempted to tamper with the transformer, possibly to steal copper or cut power. A manhunt is underway with the dog squad searching the industrial area for the unaccounted individual. title: Car launches over roundabout in Romania | 7NEWS
description: Security cameras in Romania captured a dramatic incident where a speeding car launched over a roundabout after the driver, a man in his 50s, suffered a medical episode. The driver was pulled from the wreckage with multiple fractures but no life-threatening injuries.
